The Mombasa Republican Council has requested for a meeting with security officials at the Coast. The group wants to discuss the security situation ahead of the General Election. The group wants to meet regional coordinator Nelson Marwa and all six county commissioners. &ldquo;We want to discuss how we will cooperate as citizens with the administration to ensure peace prevails before, during and after the general elections,&rdquo; officials of the group said in a statement on Friday. The statement was signed by 13 officials and members including Richard Lewa (pictured) and Randu Nzai.